## Async Readback Ring Fixes

### Problem

Previous implementation used `futures-intrusive::channel::shared::oneshot_channel()` with `try_receive()` method, which doesn't exist in futures-intrusive 0.5. The async map callback had no way to signal completion synchronously.

### Solution: Atomic Flag Polling

**ReadbackSlot extension** (crates/scriptbots-world-gfx/src/lib.rs:156):

```rust
pub struct ReadbackSlot {
    buf: wgpu::Buffer,
    ready: bool,
    mapped: std::sync::Arc<AtomicBool>,  // NEW: Shared atomic flag
}
```

**Initialization** (crates/scriptbots-world-gfx/src/lib.rs:184):

```rust
let mk_slot = || ReadbackSlot {
    buf: mk(),
    ready: false,
    mapped: std::sync::Arc::new(AtomicBool::new(false))  // Start unmapped
};
```

**Async Callback** (crates/scriptbots-world-gfx/src/lib.rs:214-216):

```rust
let mapped_flag = std::sync::Arc::clone(&slot.mapped);
slice.map_async(wgpu::MapMode::Read, move |res| {
    if res.is_ok() { mapped_flag.store(true, Ordering::Relaxed); }
});
device.poll(wgpu::Maintain::Poll);  // Flush pending work
```

**Polling in mapped()** (crates/scriptbots-world-gfx/src/lib.rs:227-232):

```rust
pub fn mapped(&mut self) -> Option<ReadbackView<'_>> {
    let prev = (self.curr + self.slots.len() - 1) % self.slots.len();
    let slot = &mut self.slots[prev];

    // Check if map callback completed
    if !slot.ready && !slot.mapped.load(Ordering::Relaxed) { return None; }

    let guard = slice.get_mapped_range();
    slot.ready = true;  // Latch ready flag
    Some(ReadbackView { guard, ... })
}
```

**Unmap on Next Copy** (crates/scriptbots-world-gfx/src/lib.rs:192-195):

```rust
pub fn copy(&mut self, ...) -> Result<(), String> {
    let slot = &mut self.slots[self.curr];

    // Unmap if still mapped from previous cycle
    if slot.mapped.load(Ordering::Relaxed) {
        slot.buf.unmap();
        slot.mapped.store(false, Ordering::Relaxed);
    }

    // ... perform copy
}
```

**Synchronization**:
- `Ordering::Relaxed`: No ordering guarantees needed; single atomic bool, no dependent operations
- `Arc` sharing: Callback closure captures clone; writes visible to main thread via atomic store
- Non-blocking: `poll()` returns immediately; readiness checked next frame

